        introduction: "Font-Romeu is a unique resort in France: perched at 1,800 m in the Cerdagne — a sun-drenched high plateau straddling France and Spain — it enjoys over 3,000 hours of sunshine per year, making it the sunniest commune in France. This peculiarity led to the installation of the Odeillo solar furnace (1,000 kW, the world's most powerful) and the National Altitude Training Centre (CNEA), where French athletes prepare for the Olympics. Font-Romeu is also a family ski resort with 43 runs and exceptional cross-country skiing. In summer, it's a hiking paradise with Lac des Bouillouses and the Cerdagne pastures. Taxis from Perpignan are used by skiing families, CNEA athletes, and tourists discovering this lesser-known corner of the Pyrenees.",
