        conseils: "In winter (December-March), the N116 can be snowy above Mont-Louis — winter tyres or chains are mandatory. Our vehicles are equipped. The Font-Romeu-Pyrénées 2000 ski area has 43 runs with guaranteed snow cover (500 snow cannons) and exceptional sunshine — you often ski in a t-shirt in March. The Odeillo solar furnace (free, 1h visit) is fascinating: a giant parabolic mirror concentrates light to reach 3,500°C. For hikers, Lac des Bouillouses (2,000 m) is accessible by shuttle from Mont-Louis in summer.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The Yellow Train of Cerdagne is a legendary tourist experience (Villefranche-Latour-de-Carol, 63 km, 3h, ~€15) but slow and doesn't serve Font-Romeu directly. The TER Perpignan-Villefranche (~€8, 50 min) goes no further. No practical direct bus. The TaxiNeo taxi at €110-140 is the only door-to-door option from Perpignan, essential with ski equipment. For 4 passengers, cost works out at €28-35 per person.",
